    narr:narration """This hub aggregates [novelty assessments](narr:RubricAssess_Novelty) evaluating the originality of framing, terminology, and metaphors across organizational artifacts. The thematic span consistently highlights a departure from generic SaaS and AI-hype language, favoring [fresh conceptual architectures](narr:RubricAssess_Novelty) like 'worldview as executable strategy' and 'narrative source of truth'. Assessors frequently contrast this [distinctive positioning](narr:RubricAssess_Novelty_1) with the [technical-narrative integration](narr:Assess_Novelty_collective_memory) of Git-as-log, noting how [IP-centric framings](narr:Assessment_Novelty_IPCrisis) ('cultivation trap', 'context squishing') avoid common domain boilerplate. While [ADR-specific assessments](narr:RubricAssess_Novelty_ADR002) acknowledge the necessity of conventional formats, they praise the avoidance of generic 'AI memory' labels in favor of 'worldview layer' terminology. Across the board, the [GTM voice](narr:RubricAssess_Novelty_GTM) and [expert-bottleneck framing](narr:Assessment_Novelty_CustomerArchitect) are credited for their high type-token ratio, though assessors consistently flag residual 'stock' phrasing—such as 'source of truth' or 'pilot-to-expand'—as the necessary cost of maintaining clarity within these novel structures.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#Assess_Novelty_cm> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#Assess_Novelty_collective_memory> ;
